# --- Submodule catch ---------------------------------------------------------
# The submodules themselves (forum/, wiki/, blog/, shop/) are tracked as
# gitlinks declared in .gitmodules. Tracked paths are immune to .gitignore,
# so these rules ONLY kick in if a submodule pointer breaks and its working
# tree suddenly becomes visible to the parent repo. In that case, `git add .`
# would otherwise pull tens of thousands of upstream files into this repo.
# Keep these patterns as a safety net and never `git add --force` around them.
/forum/**
/wiki/**
/blog/**
/shop/**

# Backups and *.original.md files written by the `compress` skill
*.original.md
*.bak
*.orig
